      "translation": "(i 1') ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001549.6",
      "line_range": "6",
      "translation": "(ii 2) He transported diorite from the mountains of Magan , fashioned his statue from it , named it for her his sake “As I am ... loved by his master , may my life be prolonged!” , and brought it before him into the E-ninnu ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001549.15",
      "line_range": "15",
      "translation": "(iii 1) Whoever erases its inscription , removes ..., or strips it from its regular offering , ( which is ) 1 sila of flour ( and ) 1 sila of husked emmer groats , may Ninĝirsu , the king of weapons , Bau , the child of An , and Ig-alima and Šul-šagana , the beloved children of Ninĝirsu , uproot him , ( and ) put an end to his lineage !"
    }
  ],
